- Joo-hyun, Bo-ra.

482
00:20:46,119 --> 00:20:47,162
- Next up…
- Wow.

483
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,748
- They're so cute.
- Yeah, so cute.

484
00:20:50,791 --> 00:20:52,334
Here are your towels. Yeah, two each.

485
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:55,504
You can use them and take them home.

486
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:57,714
Thank you. We can take them home. Nice.

487
00:20:57,798 --> 00:20:59,758
- Thank you.
- Yeah, two each.

488
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:02,511
All right, now that you've all received
your towels, as mentioned earlier,

489
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,054
- let's start with Team Ye-eun.
- Okay.

490
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:06,181
- Go ahead and choose. Wherever.
- Sure.

491
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:08,934
- Over here?
- They're heading to the end.

492
00:21:09,017 --> 00:21:11,478
- They want the ones by the bathroom.
- I'll take the one over here.

493
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:14,189
- I'll take this one, then.
- I thought you'd take this one.

494
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,733
- Team Kwang-soo, you're up.
- Okay.

495
00:21:16,817 --> 00:21:18,652
To be honest, I might snore, so…

496
00:21:18,735 --> 00:21:20,529
I'll take the corner spot,
if it's okay with you.

497
00:21:20,612 --> 00:21:23,323
By all means. I'm good with that.
Does anyone else snore?

498
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,993
Oh, that's nice.
Everyone's being considerate.

499
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:28,161
The snorers volunteered
to take corner spots.

500
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:32,040
If it's hard, we'll roll it out for you.

501
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,376
- Want some help?
- Yes, please.

502
00:21:34,459 --> 00:21:35,585
Sit tight.

503
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:36,712
Oh, thank you.

504
00:21:36,795 --> 00:21:38,380
Oh, wow!

505
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:41,174
- Hey, there's a towel on your bed.
- Is there?

506
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:42,342
- Yeah.
- What towel?

507
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:43,927
Number 23. Look.

508
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,178
Wait, what's that?

509
00:21:45,262 --> 00:21:46,847
Looks like a gift.

510
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:48,098
A GIFT?

511
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:49,391
What the…

512
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:50,809
- Just ask.
- What should we say?

513
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:52,644
- Let's ask about it.
- Excuse me.

514
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:54,646
Could you come here, please?

515
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:56,690
Oh!

516
00:21:56,773 --> 00:21:57,983
Oh, that's our little surprise!

517
00:21:58,066 --> 00:21:59,526
- It's our little surprise.
- Right.

518
00:21:59,609 --> 00:22:01,194
MY LITTLE SURPRISE

519
00:22:01,278 --> 00:22:03,655
- It's a surprise we prepared.
- Did you win the surprise gift?

520
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,949
- No, it's Dong-geon.
- Oh, Dong-geon?

521
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:08,577
Nice, Dong-geon!
Ye-eun worked really hard on that.

522
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:11,079
- Seriously?
- Hey, congratulate him.

523
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,456
YOU AGAIN…

524
00:22:12,539 --> 00:22:14,624
Can someone else switch with me?
Someone else take it.

525
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:15,834
- No, not a chance.
- No way.

526
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:18,128
No switching spots! Number 23!

527
00:22:18,211 --> 00:22:21,214
- Ye-eun put so much care into this.
- Man…

528
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:24,343
Ye-eun put the rose,
she made that heart with the rose petals…

529
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:26,011
Man, this is so funny.

530
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,722
- Go congratulate him.
- Yeah, go say congrats.

531
00:22:28,805 --> 00:22:30,599
Yeah, I guess I should.

532
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:32,017
Thank you, thank you.

533
00:22:33,643 --> 00:22:35,520
I'll go get my stuff. Okay.

534
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:41,610
All right, now, uh,
you'll need some time to unpack, right?

535
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:43,487
- Yes.
- You can do that now,

536
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:45,322
while we go and prepare
the meal for you all.

537
00:22:45,405 --> 00:22:47,199
- We'll be eating shortly.
- Okay.

538
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:48,742
You guys hungry?

539
00:22:48,825 --> 00:22:50,369
Right. Of course.

540
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:52,704
Oh, we forgot to mention this earlier.

541
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:53,872
- Yeah?
- What is it?

542
00:22:53,955 --> 00:22:55,332
- Uh…
- Hyung.

543
00:22:55,415 --> 00:22:56,875
- Uh…
- Hyung.

544
00:22:56,958 --> 00:22:58,043
What are you…

545
00:22:58,126 --> 00:23:00,087
- So the thing is…
- What is it?

546
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:02,714
…you'll get three meals a day
for the next three days.

547
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,175
These meals will be prepared
by the captains and myself.

548
00:23:06,426 --> 00:23:10,013
Since we run this B&B, your meals
and safety are our top priorities,

549
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:11,640
and we will do our absolute best.

550
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:15,477
That said, I can't guarantee anything
about our cooking skills.

551
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:18,188
- Oh, that's okay!
- Please just keep that in mind.

552
00:23:18,271 --> 00:23:19,856
- It's all right.
- You're okay with that?

553
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:21,149
Yeah!

554
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:23,318
- Meals are guaranteed, no matter what.
- Got it.

555
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:25,112
But I can't guarantee
that you'll like them.

556
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:27,072
- We like everything.
- Are you sure?

557
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:28,490
Okay, let's move on, then.

558
00:23:28,573 --> 00:23:31,159
- We have a suggestion box here.
- Okay.

559
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:34,496
If you have any suggestions,
write them down and drop them in.

560
00:23:34,579 --> 00:23:36,206
Later on, we'll collect them,

561
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,875
and we'll do our best
to accommodate what we can.

562
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:41,503
Also, you'll find
the registration form here.

563
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:43,672
Feel free to just fill in the basics.

564
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:46,508
All right, everyone, you can bring
your bags in and unpack now.

565
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,592
Okay.

566
00:23:48,385 --> 00:23:50,846
All right, so everyone fill out that form
and get some rest.

567
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:52,973
We'll let you know when the food is ready.

568
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:54,724
- Okay.
- And leave a suggestion!

569
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:56,435
All right, wish us luck!

570
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:58,395
- I think I'm spent for today.
- What?

571
00:23:58,478 --> 00:23:59,771
Really.

572
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:01,231
I'm beat.

573
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:04,526
After I introduced myself,
I was totally done for.

574
00:24:05,652 --> 00:24:06,903
Woo-seok.

575
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:08,447
Hey, you know what?

576
00:24:08,530 --> 00:24:10,949
Scratch that. We're just getting started.

577
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:13,160
Hey.

578
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:15,203
Check the rice.

579
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:17,914
Is the rice done?

580
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:19,833
- Wait, it's turned off.
- What?

581
00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:21,835
Should we open it?

582
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:26,923
Whoa!

583
00:24:31,094 --> 00:24:33,555
- Looks good, doesn't it?
- It looks pretty good. Careful.

584
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:35,807
- I think it's good.
- Besides, we've got toppings.

585
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:37,684
- Yeah, this is good.
- It is a bit…

586
00:24:38,435 --> 00:24:40,437
Put some rice here.
Let me taste it. Put it here.

587
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,314
That's good. Just a little bit.

588
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,693
OUCH, IT'S HOT

589
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:48,862
Oh, just hurry up and try it.

590
00:24:48,945 --> 00:24:49,946
PICKING IT UP AGAIN

591
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,490
FAIL

592
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:53,492
I bet it's really hot.

593
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:56,328
- We don't have time for this.
- Okay, okay, I'm trying it.

594
00:24:59,456 --> 00:25:00,540
- How is it?
- Want some help?

595
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:02,292
- Yeah.
- It turned out well.

596
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:04,377
- Wait, are you sure?
- Let's keep going.

597
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:07,672
But what are we serving this with?

598
00:25:07,756 --> 00:25:09,341
SO FAR, ALL WE HAVE IS RICE

599
00:25:09,424 --> 00:25:11,051
We're making deopbap with gochujang.

600
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:14,387
I don't know if this will ready for lunch.
Man, we should've prepped earlier.

601
00:25:14,471 --> 00:25:15,805
Hold on.

602
00:25:15,889 --> 00:25:17,891
<i>Please wait a minute</i>
<i>while we connect your call.</i>

603
00:25:17,974 --> 00:25:20,060
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Ah, yes, hello, ma'am.

604
00:25:20,143 --> 00:25:24,523
Do you think we could get about
25 servings of bulgogi to go?

605
00:25:24,606 --> 00:25:27,359
- <i>We'll make it right away.</i>
- Oh, great. Then we'll head over now.

606
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:30,320
Ma'am, sorry to ask,
but do you grill it for us, or…

607
00:25:30,403 --> 00:25:32,864
- <i>No, we can't grill it for you.</i>
- Ah, all right.

608
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:36,284
Then we'll just pick it up as is.
Please pack it to go. Thank you.

609
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:41,998
- We grill it ourselves.
- We have to grill ourselves.

610
00:25:42,082 --> 00:25:43,625
Or should we grill it
and serve right away?

611
00:25:43,708 --> 00:25:44,834
- We'll do it quick.
- Okay.

612
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:47,712
What else do we need to buy? Eggs?

613
00:25:47,796 --> 00:25:48,964
- Fried eggs?
- Eggs?

614
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:51,132
- Gim?
- Gim sounds good.

615
00:25:51,216 --> 00:25:53,260
Let's just buy some gim and eggs.

616
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:55,178
- Then Ye-eun and Woo-seok?
- Yeah.

617
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:57,055
- You two stay here and get that going.
- Got it.

618
00:25:57,138 --> 00:25:58,515
Kwang-soo and I will go.

619
00:26:03,478 --> 00:26:05,605
SUDDENLY FEELING RUSHED

620
00:26:10,235 --> 00:26:11,236
Gosh.

621
00:26:11,319 --> 00:26:14,698
Here we go. Man, this is stressful
all of a sudden.

622
00:26:14,781 --> 00:26:17,617
We'll stop by the supermarket
and get the eggs first.

623
00:26:17,701 --> 00:26:19,452
Eggs. Kim… Kimchi.

624
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,079
Okay.

625
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:25,041
Wait, what about dinner?

626
00:26:26,876 --> 00:26:30,380
Let's just get through lunch first.
But honestly, at his rate,

627
00:26:30,463 --> 00:26:34,259
I feel like we're just gonna be cooking
meals the entire time we're here.

628
00:26:34,342 --> 00:26:36,094
We'll have to cook first thing.

629
00:26:36,177 --> 00:26:38,597
We'll have to cook, go to bed,
then do it all over again.

630
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,806
Wow.

631
00:26:43,351 --> 00:26:44,686
- Hello.
- Hello.

632
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:47,105
- Hi, there.
- Um, feel free to take a look around.

633
00:26:47,188 --> 00:26:48,857
- Oh, okay. Thank you.
- No problem.

634
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:52,319
- Whoa, he really is handsome.
- Right?

635
00:26:52,402 --> 00:26:53,862
He's super handsome.

636
00:26:55,238 --> 00:26:56,948
Everyone seems settled in.

637
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:58,825
"Things you want to do at the B&B."

638
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:02,245
Mmm… talk all night?

639
00:27:02,329 --> 00:27:05,081
I want kimchi bokkeumbap. Kimchi jjim too.

640
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:07,626
EVERYONE IS FILLING OUT
THEIR FORMS

641
00:27:07,709 --> 00:27:10,295
Unni, what do you… Oh, my gosh!

642
00:27:12,047 --> 00:27:14,174
- Oh, man!
- I forgot how handsome he is.

643
00:27:14,257 --> 00:27:15,383
Hi, everyone.

644
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:16,843
HAS A KNACK FOR STARTLING PEOPLE

645
00:27:16,926 --> 00:27:18,553
Anyone need anything over here?

646
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:20,847
Wow, look at him. He's so pretty.

647
00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:25,685
- Anything at all?
- Shouldn't you be cooking?

648
00:27:25,769 --> 00:27:27,228
- Food, right.
- Yeah.

649
00:27:27,312 --> 00:27:29,356
- We're hungry.
- We're working on it.

650
00:27:30,023 --> 00:27:31,566
But it's going to take a little while.

651
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:34,486
So if you're really hungry,
you should just feel free to grab

652
00:27:34,569 --> 00:27:36,571
- something from the snack bar.
- Sounds good.

653
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,740
And, of course, if you have
any questions or anything…

654
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:41,368
Oh, so these slippers are
just for indoors, right?

655
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:44,454
- Yeah, just indoors.
- We shouldn't wear them to the bathroom?

656
00:27:44,537 --> 00:27:45,997
Yes, I think that would be best.

657
00:27:46,665 --> 00:27:48,166
FOR A GUEST TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM

658
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,752
1) TAKE OFF SLIPPERS

659
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:53,963
2) CHANGE INTO THEIR OWN SHOES

660
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:55,924
3) SWITCH BACK INTO SLIPPERS

661
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:58,468
INCONVENIENT

662
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:00,970
It might be a little inconvenient,
so I'll look into it.

663
00:28:01,054 --> 00:28:03,264
- Okay.
- I'll check on it and let you know.

664
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:05,141
- Okay, thanks.
- You're the best, Woo-seok!

665
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,309
Thanks.

666
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:09,437
Who's that?

667
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:10,522
Byeon Woo-seok.

668
00:28:10,605 --> 00:28:11,773
Hey, Woo-seok.

669
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,984
- <i>Hyung, um, we got a complaint.</i>
- Already?

670
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:18,863
HEART DROPS

671
00:28:18,947 --> 00:28:22,325
<i>So, we have everyone wearing</i>
<i>indoor slippers, right?</i>

672
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:24,411
- Right.
- <i>But since the bathroom is outside,</i>

673
00:28:24,494 --> 00:28:26,454
<i>I think they find it</i>
<i>a little inconvenient.</i>

674
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:29,374
- Ah-ha… I see.
- What should we do?

675
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:32,168
We could buy bathroom slippers.
They sell those at the supermarket, right?

676
00:28:32,252 --> 00:28:35,797
- Right. We'll buy some extra slippers.
- Yeah, we'll buy some bathroom slippers.

677
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:36,923
<i>Okay, got it.</i>

678
00:28:37,841 --> 00:28:39,884
See? There's always something.

679
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:42,887
- That didn't even cross our minds.
- Yes, exactly.

680
00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:45,014
Wearing the same slippers
in both might feel a bit…

681
00:28:45,098 --> 00:28:47,058
It's because that place
used to be a gymnasium.

682
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,268
Right, of course.

683
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:51,896
- Man, I'm starving. Oh, boy.
- Yeah, me too.

684
00:28:52,939 --> 00:28:54,107
We haven't eaten yet.

685
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:55,692
CURRENT TIME 12:00 P.M.

686
00:28:55,775 --> 00:28:56,943
I mean…

687
00:28:57,861 --> 00:28:59,946
- Yeah?
- …this is a B&B, right?

688
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,991
But other than eating and washing dishes…

689
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:04,784
What?

690
00:29:04,868 --> 00:29:05,869
Well…

691
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:10,206
we need time to actually do stuff.

692
00:29:11,416 --> 00:29:14,669
First off, let's just focus
on getting food on the table.

693
00:29:16,671 --> 00:29:18,465
Man, we're pressed for time.

694
00:29:18,548 --> 00:29:19,591
Okay.

695
00:29:20,175 --> 00:29:21,718
- What time is it?
- Five past 12:00.

696
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:24,471
- If we move fast, we can eat at 1:00?
- Yeah, let's move fast.

697
00:29:24,554 --> 00:29:25,638
LET'S AIM TO SERVE FOOD
IN 1 HOUR!

698
00:29:25,722 --> 00:29:26,723
Kimchi.

699
00:29:27,974 --> 00:29:31,102
- The kimchi we had last time was good.
- It was over there somewhere.

700
00:29:31,186 --> 00:29:32,771
Huh? Oh, here it is.

701
00:29:32,854 --> 00:29:33,855
Where?

702
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:36,399
What did we have last time?
That kimchi was good.

703
00:29:36,483 --> 00:29:37,901
Just buy whatever.

704
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,111
- This isn't it?
- No.

705
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:43,573
- Got it.
- But, Hyung, this is…

706
00:29:43,656 --> 00:29:44,657
Yeah?

707
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:48,244
We need to buy 25 servings of the kimchi.

708
00:29:48,912 --> 00:29:50,705
- This is just…
- For crying out loud.

709
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:52,165
WILL THIS BE ENOUGH
FOR 25 SERVINGS?

710
00:29:52,999 --> 00:29:54,083
Man, this is…

711
00:29:58,046 --> 00:30:00,715
- Okay, this is it.
- And you thought we could run a B&B?

712
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:05,845
What's next?
How are we supposed to do this?

713
00:30:05,929 --> 00:30:07,472
How are we supposed to survive three days?

714
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:09,349
I've never fed
20-something people in my life.

715
00:30:09,432 --> 00:30:12,310
- I mean, this is ridiculous.
- Hey, Kwang-soo. I see eggs.

716
00:30:12,393 --> 00:30:14,187
Is this much kimchi enough?

717
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:15,271
Oh, God.

718
00:30:21,528 --> 00:30:22,779
Hey, Kwang-soo.

719
00:30:23,363 --> 00:30:26,074
- That should be enough, right?
- Okay. No, wait.

720
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,160
Gim, gim, gim!

721
00:30:30,286 --> 00:30:32,205
NEXT UP, GIM

722
00:30:32,914 --> 00:30:34,290
Hey, hey, Kwang-soo.

723
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:37,126
I've never bought this much
at a supermarket before.

724
00:30:37,210 --> 00:30:39,796
- Hey, look at all this, man. Whoa.
- Hey, Hyung.

725
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:41,130
Hurry up.

726
00:30:41,214 --> 00:30:42,715
- What's next?
- Slippers.

727
00:30:43,883 --> 00:30:44,884
Oh, boy.

728
00:30:45,635 --> 00:30:47,887
- Where are they? Right here.
- Oh, there they are.

729
00:30:50,265 --> 00:30:53,852
- We need at least ten of these, don't we?
- If not more.

730
00:30:57,438 --> 00:30:59,357
BACK IN THE QUAGMIRE OF NUMBERS…

731
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:02,360
But if it's for the bathroom,
we need at least 20.

732
00:31:02,443 --> 00:31:04,362
Don't you think that's too many?

733
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:07,073
If it's one per person,
then we'd have to write names on them.

734
00:31:07,156 --> 00:31:08,867
- Sounds like a hassle.
- Just buy them.

735
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:10,368
- You sure?
- Just buy them.

736
00:31:10,451 --> 00:31:13,329
Wait. Come on, listen to me.
People don't pee at the same time.

737
00:31:13,413 --> 00:31:14,664
They don't all…

738
00:31:14,747 --> 00:31:16,165
Okay, fine. Let's go.

739
00:31:16,249 --> 00:31:17,500
Let's just buy this many.

740
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:19,711
Oh, we need this.

741
00:31:19,794 --> 00:31:21,087
For the coffee.

742
00:31:22,088 --> 00:31:25,049
If we're going to put coffee out,
we'll need something to…

743
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:28,094
What if we use this?
An electric coffee pot.

744
00:31:28,177 --> 00:31:30,847
But if we get that,
then we'd have to clean it.

745
00:31:30,930 --> 00:31:33,224
Then we can just clean it.
We can just clean it!

746
00:31:33,308 --> 00:31:35,351
Do you know how much work we already have?

747
00:31:35,435 --> 00:31:37,562
No, I mean, we can split tasks
and have one of us clean it.

748
00:31:37,645 --> 00:31:39,772
Here, gimme those. You bring that over.

749
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:44,736
- Did we get everything?
- Yeah, we got everything on the list.

750
00:31:44,819 --> 00:31:47,071
- Good.
- Hold on.

751
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:48,615
Oh, I'm sorry. It's a lot.

752
00:31:48,698 --> 00:31:50,074
No, it's fine.

753
00:31:50,158 --> 00:31:51,993
- Oh, thank you.
- No problem.

754
00:31:52,076 --> 00:31:54,495
- Carry the fragile items.
- Cash or card?

755
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,331
Oh, that's right.

756
00:31:56,414 --> 00:31:57,749
- Hyung.
- Sorry about that.

757
00:31:57,832 --> 00:31:59,125
Get it together, man.

758
00:31:59,208 --> 00:32:00,877
I'm all over the place. Gimme a slap!

759
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:02,921
GET IT TOGETHER

760
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:05,006
I'm really all over the place.
I'm out of it.

761
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:07,425
I can't get it together.
I'm not even joking.

762
00:32:07,508 --> 00:32:10,136
- We need lunch by 1:00 at the latest.
- I don't think we'll make it

763
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:11,220
- by 1:00.
- Just go.

764
00:32:11,304 --> 00:32:13,181
Hello, ma'am.
We ordered some pork earlier.

765
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:15,433
- Oh, the order. Come this way.
- Where is it?

766
00:32:15,516 --> 00:32:17,560
- Please come this way. Give me one sec.
- Smells great.

767
00:32:17,644 --> 00:32:19,646
- Of course.
- Wow, that smells so good.

768
00:32:19,729 --> 00:32:21,648
Man, I'm exhausted.
Kwang-soo, look, there's coffee.

769
00:32:21,731 --> 00:32:23,107
Thirty servings.

770
00:32:24,317 --> 00:32:27,153
TIME FOR A CAFFEINE BOOST

771
00:32:28,196 --> 00:32:29,364
Oh, man.

772
00:32:31,699 --> 00:32:33,326
- This is nice.
- It is.

773
00:32:34,494 --> 00:32:36,454
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Goodbye.

774
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:42,919
We need to wrap this up by 1:00
or 1:15 at the latest, right?

775
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:45,171
Yeah, we can try.

776
00:32:46,297 --> 00:32:49,342
Hey, how's it going?
What have you been up to?

777
00:32:49,425 --> 00:32:51,594
- We're decorating the board.
- Oh!

778
00:32:51,678 --> 00:32:53,763
It's kind of turned into a contest
over who decorates

779
00:32:53,846 --> 00:32:56,557
their team captain's name the fanciest.

780
00:32:56,641 --> 00:32:58,017
- Oh, wow.
- We went all out.

781
00:32:58,101 --> 00:32:59,811
So cute. I love it.

782
00:32:59,894 --> 00:33:01,145
I love mine.

783
00:33:01,729 --> 00:33:02,730
Really?

784
00:33:02,814 --> 00:33:04,816
- We've taken a ton of photos.
- Wow.

785
00:33:06,109 --> 00:33:07,360
Wow!

786
00:33:07,443 --> 00:33:09,070
DONG-GEON, HYO-JUNG,
SEONG-JOON LET'S GO!

787
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:10,905
AE-YEONG, EUN-JUNG,
HYEONG-SEON, KOSONI

788
00:33:12,615 --> 00:33:14,200
Wow, it's so nice out.

789
00:33:14,283 --> 00:33:15,284
Twenty.

790
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:16,411
Whoa!

791
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:19,956
Are you sure you're doing it right?

792
00:33:20,039 --> 00:33:21,791
Oh, my mom. Hello?

793
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:23,793
Hey, Mom.

794
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:25,753
You know where Dong-geon is?

795
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:28,339
Mom, he's here at the B&B.

796
00:33:29,465 --> 00:33:31,718
I was so surprised to see him here.

797
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:35,430
I guess he applied
because he wanted to come.

798
00:33:35,513 --> 00:33:36,514
Yeah.

799
00:33:36,597 --> 00:33:39,726
Seriously, him being here
is stressing me out.

800
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:44,647
Wait, Mom, here he comes. He's right here.

801
00:33:46,190 --> 00:33:48,443
Why didn't you tell Mom anything?

802
00:33:49,152 --> 00:33:50,737
Who submitted you?

803
00:33:51,654 --> 00:33:54,032
I did, but I didn't know you'd be here.

804
00:33:54,115 --> 00:33:55,366
You didn't know?

805
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:56,451
No.

806
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:57,702
SHRINKS
(GUEST ALERT)

807
00:33:57,785 --> 00:34:00,038
- You really didn't know?
- I didn't.

808
00:34:00,121 --> 00:34:02,790
- When did you find out?
- Uh, when the article came out.

809
00:34:02,874 --> 00:34:04,876
- Did you interview?
- Yeah, in the summer.

810
00:34:04,959 --> 00:34:07,128
- And you said you were my brother?
- No.

811
00:34:08,046 --> 00:34:09,964
I didn't know it was your show.

812
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:11,049
Really?

813
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:15,511
Do you know what time
we'll be having lunch?

814
00:34:15,595 --> 00:34:18,347
Do you know what time
we'll be having lunch?

815
00:34:18,431 --> 00:34:21,267
It should probably be
in about 40 or 50 minutes.

816
00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:22,351
Oh, sure.

817
00:34:22,435 --> 00:34:24,854
- You might wanna grab a small snack.
- Got it.

818
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:30,735
Hey, Kkoedori.

819
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:35,114
- I love this stuff.
- Yeah, that cooler is totally stocked.

820
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:37,533
Great. You had this?

821
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:38,618
It's good.

822
00:34:38,701 --> 00:34:40,161
You eat junk food?

823
00:34:40,244 --> 00:34:41,245
Yeah, I love it.

824
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,872
- So you really eat snacks?
- I love snacks.

825
00:34:42,955 --> 00:34:43,998
Oh, really?

826
00:34:44,082 --> 00:34:45,625
You don't seem like the type.

827
00:34:45,708 --> 00:34:49,962
I try to eat well, but I work out too.
So if I eat more than usual,

828
00:34:50,046 --> 00:34:52,632
- I'll work out a little longer.
- Right.

829
00:34:52,715 --> 00:34:54,926
AFTER THE SMALL TALK,
STRAIGHT TO DOING DISHES

830
00:34:56,719 --> 00:34:58,554
- You're doing the dishes now?
- I can't believe it!

831
00:34:58,638 --> 00:34:59,806
Huh? What?

832
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,558
- I thought you'd be cooking.
- He must not be the cook.

833
00:35:02,642 --> 00:35:03,976
Oh, no, I mean…

834
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:08,147
Everyone's out… buying some stuff.
I'm going to cook later.

835
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:10,441
- Later.
- You got this.

836
00:35:10,525 --> 00:35:11,776
- Good luck.
- All right.

837
00:35:11,859 --> 00:35:13,361
AFTER THE GUESTS LEAVE

838
00:35:13,444 --> 00:35:15,530
MAKES A CALL RIGHT AWAY

839
00:35:15,613 --> 00:35:17,115
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Yeah?

840
00:35:17,198 --> 00:35:19,450
- <i>Hyung, there's a big problem.</i>
- What?

841
00:35:19,534 --> 00:35:22,161
They think
we're actually cooking everything.

842
00:35:22,245 --> 00:35:24,205
- Yeah, of course they do.
- Listen.

843
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:27,125
Don't say anything unnecessary.
Let's go with that.

844
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,918
- Don't overthink this.
- <i>I didn't say anything.</i>

845
00:35:29,001 --> 00:35:30,128
Just focus on one thing:

846
00:35:30,211 --> 00:35:32,588
We're providing them
with a delicious meal.

847
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:33,965
That's all they need to know.

848
00:35:34,048 --> 00:35:35,591
(THOUGH IT MAY BE PREMADE)

849
00:35:35,675 --> 00:35:37,218
I'm not telling you to lie.

850
00:35:37,301 --> 00:35:39,220
Just don't say anything unless they ask.

851
00:35:39,303 --> 00:35:41,222
- No, I won't. I didn't say anything.
- Okay, good.

852
00:35:41,305 --> 00:35:42,473
Good. We're headed back.

853
00:35:42,557 --> 00:35:44,308
So where is everyone now?

854
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:46,227
They're all outside.

855
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:48,187
They're just walking around and stuff.

856
00:35:49,313 --> 00:35:53,109
Then I'll drive the car all the way inside
so they don't see anything.

857
00:35:53,192 --> 00:35:55,153
<i>Yeah, that's better.</i>
<i>It'll look less suspicious.</i>

858
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:57,613
- Let's keep it natural.
- <i>Yeah, you're right.</i>

859
00:35:59,574 --> 00:36:00,700
We're here.

860
00:36:01,409 --> 00:36:03,703
- Drive in as far as you can.
- Okay, I got it.

861
00:36:03,786 --> 00:36:05,621
Nice and easy.

862
00:36:05,705 --> 00:36:09,125
- I'm gonna pull in there and back up.
- Wait, the dining area's packed?

863
00:36:09,208 --> 00:36:10,710
- Oh my gosh, they're all outside.
- Oh, man.

864
00:36:10,793 --> 00:36:12,628
- I bet he was really freaked out.
- That's crazy.

865
00:36:12,712 --> 00:36:14,297
Hey look, they're here!

866
00:36:14,380 --> 00:36:17,091
- Huh? They went out?
- They went grocery shopping.

867
00:36:17,175 --> 00:36:18,968
Looks like they're back
with the groceries.

868
00:36:19,051 --> 00:36:20,720
Oh, I see.

869
00:36:20,803 --> 00:36:24,432
So then, that means they haven't
even started cooking yet, right?

870
00:36:24,515 --> 00:36:25,516
I guess so.

871
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:27,852
They're looking over here. Careful.

872
00:36:27,935 --> 00:36:28,936
Tell you what.

873
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:32,356
I'll turn the car around and back up.
If they look this way, the game is up.

874
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,983
They're still looking.

875
00:36:34,567 --> 00:36:36,611
WOO-SEOK SNEAKS UP AND WAITS

876
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:43,075
- We bought gim!
- Hang on.

877
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,452
I'll cover it with this.

878
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:45,661
THE GIM SHIELD

879
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:50,708
They're coming, they're coming.

880
00:36:51,334 --> 00:36:54,045
- They're coming, they're coming.
- Do you need any help?

881
00:36:54,128 --> 00:36:56,505
No, it's fine, it's fine.
Just stay put. No, stop.

882
00:36:56,589 --> 00:36:59,425
- You can help us later.
- You're a good guy, Dong-geon.

883
00:36:59,508 --> 00:37:01,636
Just stay put over there.
We're all good here.

884
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:04,764
- We'll ask for your help very shortly.
- Okay, let us know.

885
00:37:04,847 --> 00:37:07,350
Just rest for now.
I mean, it's a B&B, after all.

886
00:37:07,433 --> 00:37:09,560
- Lunch will be ready soon!
- That's right.

887
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:16,442
- All done.
- Why are they hanging out right there?

888
00:37:16,525 --> 00:37:19,070
I can't wait to see what they make for us.

889
00:37:19,153 --> 00:37:21,239
- Did you guys eat something?
- Oh, yes.

890
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:23,407
Ah, that's great. Communal slippers.

891
00:37:23,491 --> 00:37:26,452
For your convenience
when going to the bathroom.

892
00:37:27,161 --> 00:37:29,121
- So, I bought these for you guys.
- Just what we needed.

893
00:37:29,205 --> 00:37:31,582
Do me a favor and put them out front,
will you?

894
00:37:31,666 --> 00:37:34,126
Thank you.

895
00:37:34,210 --> 00:37:35,878
CURRENT TIME 12:50 P.M.

896
00:37:35,962 --> 00:37:37,380
It'll be ready soon.

897
00:37:37,463 --> 00:37:40,675
It'll just be 25 minutes,
then we can eat, okay?

898
00:37:40,758 --> 00:37:42,343
They seem really hungry.

899
00:37:42,426 --> 00:37:45,054
I know. They keep circling around
the dining area like vultures.

900
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,598
- I'm hungry.
- Yeah, me too.

901
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:50,184
- I'll start on the eggs right now.
- Okay.

902
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:51,686
I'll start grilling.

903
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:52,770
RICE, GOCHUJANG
SAMGYEOPSAL,

904
00:37:52,853 --> 00:37:53,854
FRIED EGG, KIMCHI, GIM

905
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:56,065
Which oil should I use? Olive oil?

906
00:37:56,649 --> 00:37:58,359
Anything. Just use anything.

907
00:37:58,442 --> 00:38:00,945
- Speed is the most important thing now.
- Okay.

908
00:38:01,904 --> 00:38:04,115
PICKS OUT A COOKING OIL
AT RANDOM

909
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:07,368
We should set out the dishes too, right?

910
00:38:07,451 --> 00:38:08,744
Don't you think?

911
00:38:11,664 --> 00:38:13,291
GOCHUJANG BULGOGI HEAD CHEF

912
00:38:15,543 --> 00:38:17,295
TURN ON THE STOVE FIRST

913
00:38:18,879 --> 00:38:20,298
Whoa, this is legit.

914
00:38:27,805 --> 00:38:30,266
BOOSTS HYDRATION
BEFORE OFFICIALLY COOKING

915
00:38:30,349 --> 00:38:32,184
- Whoa, hey!
- Huh?

916
00:38:32,268 --> 00:38:33,311
- Oh, my goodness!
- Oh!

917
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:34,895
WHITE SMOKE IS RISING
FROM THE WOK

918
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:36,522
- Oh, my goodness!
- Oh!

919
00:38:38,149 --> 00:38:39,608
Whoa, hey!

920
00:38:39,692 --> 00:38:40,860
Oh, my goodness!

921
00:38:41,902 --> 00:38:43,070
Oh, my goodness!

922
00:38:43,696 --> 00:38:44,947
Everything's fine!

923
00:38:46,073 --> 00:38:47,533
Kwang-soo, hurry up.

924
00:38:47,616 --> 00:38:49,994
STARTS GRILLING
AS IF NOTHING HAPPENED

925
00:38:55,583 --> 00:38:56,584
Oh, no!

926
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:03,966
ALL HE DID WAS PUT MEAT
IN THE PAN

927
00:39:04,675 --> 00:39:05,801
AND NOW IT'S CHARRED BLACK

928
00:39:05,885 --> 00:39:07,470
Wait a second. I'll do it.

929
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:11,557
What's going on?

930
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:13,225
It's nothing.

931
00:39:13,309 --> 00:39:15,936
Why was it doing that? Why was it on fire?

932
00:39:16,020 --> 00:39:18,147
- This batch is burnt.
- Aren't you supposed to use that?

933
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,357
I don't understand.

934
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,816
This much is okay.

935
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:22,109
GOCHUJANG SAMGYEOPSAL,
THE DISASTER EDITION

936
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:23,944
- That won't work.
- What? Why?

937
00:39:25,404 --> 00:39:27,156
What's wrong? Oh, shoot.

938
00:39:27,239 --> 00:39:29,408
- Don't worry, Hyung. I got it now.
- Move, move.

939
00:39:29,492 --> 00:39:30,910
It's because its marinated.

940
00:39:30,993 --> 00:39:33,245
Oh, it's the sauce. Hold on.

941
00:39:33,329 --> 00:39:34,872
I'll just jump in and help.

942
00:39:34,955 --> 00:39:36,749
- It's a two-man job.
- Yeah, I got it.

943
00:39:39,835 --> 00:39:41,045
Be quick!

944
00:39:42,004 --> 00:39:44,590
Man, what are we gonna do?
This burns so fast.

945
00:39:44,673 --> 00:39:46,300
THE GOCHUJANG BULGOGI
KEEPS BURNING

946
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:48,427
The gochujang sauce
is making it hard, right?

947
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:50,388
Oh, no. What now?

948
00:39:51,055 --> 00:39:53,682
The sauce keeps burning
before the meat's even cooked.

949
00:39:54,475 --> 00:39:56,769
We'll just have to keep wiping as we go.

950
00:39:57,937 --> 00:39:59,688
Something's burning. I hope they're okay.

951
00:39:59,772 --> 00:40:01,232
THE BURNT SMELL
REACHES THE GUESTS

952
00:40:03,317 --> 00:40:04,610
Uh-oh.

953
00:40:04,693 --> 00:40:06,821
Uh, don't worry.
We still have plenty of time.

954
00:40:06,904 --> 00:40:08,948
- Smells good, right?
- Yeah.

955
00:40:09,031 --> 00:40:10,699
Just a little longer.

956
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:13,119
- We've been prepping since yesterday.
- Oh, boy.

957
00:40:13,202 --> 00:40:14,203
It's all good.

958
00:40:16,038 --> 00:40:17,039
What time is it?

959
00:40:17,123 --> 00:40:18,707
Now? It's 1:07.

960
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:20,042
- Yeah, 1:07.
- Yeah.

961
00:40:20,126 --> 00:40:22,128
- He said 1:15.
- Think it'll be ready by then?

962
00:40:22,211 --> 00:40:23,462
TIME LEFT UNTIL SERVING

963
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:25,256
Wait. It's burning too much.

964
00:40:25,339 --> 00:40:27,133
How are we going to cook all this?

965
00:40:27,591 --> 00:40:29,718
STILL A MOUNTAIN OF MEAT LEFT

966
00:40:30,469 --> 00:40:32,138
This isn't gonna work.

967
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:34,223
AND THE MEAT KEEPS BURNING

968
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:36,809
I was so flustered.

969
00:40:36,892 --> 00:40:39,061
I wasn't sure what to do
since the meat kept burning.

970
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:41,730
None of us had ever experienced
anything like it.

971
00:40:41,814 --> 00:40:43,232
This isn't gonna work.

972
00:40:43,941 --> 00:40:45,568
- Man, this is bad.
- What's wrong?

973
00:40:45,651 --> 00:40:48,028
- Well--
- Are these burnt too?

974
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:50,072
- I think the fried eggs are cooked.
- I know.

975
00:40:50,156 --> 00:40:51,407
You have to add oil.

976
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,326
I did add oil, but…

977
00:40:54,410 --> 00:40:56,829
At this rate,
we'll be in tears by dinnertime.

978
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:02,501
Wow. I never thought
I'd find myself crying here.

979
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:03,752
36 HOURS LATER

980
00:41:03,836 --> 00:41:06,297
Don't be surprised if I disappear
in the middle of the night.

981
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:08,382
18 HOURS LATER

982
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,592
- Where did he go?
- Jae-seok!

983
00:41:09,675 --> 00:41:11,760
- I don't believe it.
- This is all my fault.

984
00:41:11,844 --> 00:41:14,138
We have to start prepping dinner
right after this.

985
00:41:14,221 --> 00:41:15,473
What are we gonna make?

986
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:18,225
I don't know.
Let's not think about that right now.

987
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:19,560
This feels hopeless.

988
00:41:19,643 --> 00:41:21,395
How are you supposed
to get this evenly cooked?

989
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:23,689
Let's stay calm.
Just breathe and stay focused.

990
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:27,401
Let's get it together.

991
00:41:28,194 --> 00:41:29,778
Stay calm, everybody.

992
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:31,572
It's fine not to use any oil.

993
00:41:31,655 --> 00:41:34,575
- No oil?
- I think that's why it's burning.

994
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:37,203
Cook it on low. Don't use high heat.

995
00:41:40,915 --> 00:41:42,166
Ye-eun, it's done. Look.

996
00:41:42,249 --> 00:41:44,919
- Yeah, it's done. I think that looks good.
- Just don't add oil.

997
00:41:46,545 --> 00:41:49,089
So you cook it over low heat like this…

998
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:51,091
Turn it up a bit. Medium should be fine.

999
00:41:51,175 --> 00:41:53,302
Kwang-soo, put it on medium.

1000
00:41:53,385 --> 00:41:55,513
It was burning because of the oil.

1001
00:41:55,596 --> 00:41:57,389
Right, because pork belly already has fat.

1002
00:41:57,473 --> 00:41:59,683
That's right. Who added the oil?

1003
00:42:01,435 --> 00:42:03,354
You need some oil so it doesn't stick.

1004
00:42:07,608 --> 00:42:09,735
Oh, yeah, that's it.
It smells really good.

1005
00:42:09,818 --> 00:42:11,862
- Looks done. Hey, it's done.
- It's done?

1006
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:14,156
- Woo-seok, you just focus on the eggs.
- Oh, okay.

1007
00:42:17,493 --> 00:42:18,536
Wow.

1008
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:19,870
There's a lot here.

1009
00:42:20,663 --> 00:42:22,581
Although they look a bit rough.

1010
00:42:22,665 --> 00:42:25,793
- It's a mess, isn't it?
- Hey, it's fine. We'll have to make do.

1011
00:42:26,460 --> 00:42:28,879
Man, I should really learn how to cook.

1012
00:42:29,964 --> 00:42:32,841
- Let me try cooking the meat just in case.
- Are you done with that?

1013
00:42:32,925 --> 00:42:36,554
No, I just feel like I'm not doing
a good job with the eggs.

1014
00:42:36,637 --> 00:42:38,472
- Should I do the eggs?
- Yeah, sure.

1015
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:40,474
Maybe it's because
you're on a cooking show, Ye-eun.

1016
00:42:40,558 --> 00:42:43,394
- Right. I am on a cooking show. Yeah.
- You're surprisingly calm.

1017
00:42:43,477 --> 00:42:44,603
True.

1018
00:42:44,687 --> 00:42:47,982
- Can I get that tray over here?
- I'll wash it and hand it over.

1019
00:42:48,065 --> 00:42:51,193
- Oppa, you need more eggs, right?
- Yeah, I think I'll need more.

1020
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:58,158
PROFESSIONAL KITCHEN WORKER

1021
00:42:58,242 --> 00:42:59,410
HAHAHA!

1022
00:42:59,493 --> 00:43:01,620
I think they're starting
to make friends already.

1023
00:43:01,704 --> 00:43:03,330
Yeah, and their energy is amazing.

1024
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:05,124
- Yeah, totally.
- They're so excited.

1025
00:43:05,207 --> 00:43:06,333
You're so unhinged!

1026
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:08,085
GUESTS FULL OF ENERGY

1027
00:43:08,168 --> 00:43:10,129
GUESTS ON ENERGY OVERLOAD

1028
00:43:10,212 --> 00:43:12,089
Hey, hey, hey!

1029
00:43:12,172 --> 00:43:15,134
- How much longer could lunch take?
- I know, right?

1030
00:43:15,217 --> 00:43:17,136
There was a bunch of smoke before.
It's a mess.

1031
00:43:17,219 --> 00:43:18,887
- There was, right?
- Let's go check it out.

1032
00:43:18,971 --> 00:43:20,222
Okay!

1033
00:43:21,765 --> 00:43:24,351
CURRENT TIME
(5 MINUTES PAST PROMISED TIME)

1034
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:26,061
But we still have a lot left.

1035
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:28,230
I think this should be
around ten servings.

1036
00:43:28,314 --> 00:43:29,857
Ten servings done.

1037
00:43:31,025 --> 00:43:33,861
But if they come eat now,
ten servings will be gone in no time.

1038
00:43:34,653 --> 00:43:36,238
- Low heat, like before.
- Okay.

1039
00:43:36,322 --> 00:43:39,450
Should we say 1:30 sharp?
Is that too early?

1040
00:43:39,533 --> 00:43:42,286
- Should we tell them?
- How about 1:40?

1041
00:43:42,369 --> 00:43:43,412
1:30 should be good.

1042
00:43:43,495 --> 00:43:45,205
- Are you sure?
- 1:35.

1043
00:43:46,165 --> 00:43:48,417
No, 1:30. Hold on a second.

1044
00:43:51,545 --> 00:43:54,715
Okay, tell them
we'll start serving at 1:40.

1045
00:43:54,798 --> 00:43:57,718
- So, 40 past?
- Yeah, stir-fried pork bibimbap.

1046
00:43:58,761 --> 00:44:00,846
- What's the real name of the dish?
- Stir-fried pork.

1047
00:44:00,929 --> 00:44:02,264
It's gochujang bulgogi, no?

1048
00:44:02,348 --> 00:44:03,641
Gochujang pork.

1049
00:44:03,724 --> 00:44:05,601
Just call it gochujang stir-fried pork.

1050
00:44:05,684 --> 00:44:08,520
If we call it gochujang bulgogi,
they'll know we bought it.

1051
00:44:10,773 --> 00:44:13,692
Hey, just call it meat-deopbap.
Meat-deopbap it is.

1052
00:44:13,776 --> 00:44:15,569
- That sounds good.
- Meat-deopbap?

1053
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:18,322
- Yeah.
- We'll start serving at 40 past. 40 past.

1054
00:44:18,405 --> 00:44:20,574
- Okay. Yay!
- Gochujang.

1055
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:22,868
What was it again?
Gochujang bulgogi-deopbap?

1056
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:25,788
Meat-deopbap?
The menu's meat-deopbap. Yep.

1057
00:44:25,871 --> 00:44:27,414
Ooh, sounds tasty.

1058
00:44:27,498 --> 00:44:30,000
- We can't have any more delays.
- I know. We're good.

1059
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:32,086
Hyung, how's this?

1060
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:33,879
- Looks done.
- Yeah, looks good.

1061
00:44:33,962 --> 00:44:36,507
- It looks good.
- Okay, almost done.

1062
00:44:37,966 --> 00:44:40,094
- You're good at this Mr. Byeon.
- Thank you.

1063
00:44:41,345 --> 00:44:43,055
Doesn't this feel like a shoulder workout?

1064
00:44:43,138 --> 00:44:46,642
Yeah, my shoulder blades!
My shoulders and wrists are killing me.

1065
00:44:46,725 --> 00:44:48,644
- The forearms.
- Yeah, forearms too.

1066
00:44:51,188 --> 00:44:53,982
Wow, cooking's hard
even with prepped ingredients.

1067
00:44:54,066 --> 00:44:56,402
If it were three to four servings,
we'd be done already.

1068
00:44:56,485 --> 00:44:58,237
- Exactly.
- It'd be no big deal.

1069
00:44:58,320 --> 00:45:01,407
But cooking for a group of 20 people
is no easy task.

1070
00:45:02,324 --> 00:45:05,411
Still, seeing them enjoy the food
will feel so satisfying.

1071
00:45:05,494 --> 00:45:08,872
- Right.
- A good meal makes all the difference.

1072
00:45:08,956 --> 00:45:10,708
- It's really true.
- Right, right.

1073
00:45:10,791 --> 00:45:12,835
- That's right.
- I just hope it tastes good.

1074
00:45:12,918 --> 00:45:14,920
- Same here.
- Wow, it's almost full.

1075
00:45:15,003 --> 00:45:17,131
Hey, I think we can finish by 1:40.

1076
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:18,507
Yeah, I think so.

1077
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:20,426
SET UP THE GIM

1078
00:45:20,509 --> 00:45:22,136
SET UP THE WARMER

1079
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:23,804
TODAY'S MENU

1080
00:45:24,888 --> 00:45:26,724
GIM, FRIED EGGS

1081
00:45:27,725 --> 00:45:29,101
Hey, it's 1:40.

1082
00:45:29,184 --> 00:45:31,228
- It's 1:40.
- Is it time to eat yet?

1083
00:45:31,311 --> 00:45:33,856
- Can we go in now?
- Forty? Yes, come on in!

1084
00:45:33,939 --> 00:45:36,358
Did he say we could go?

1085
00:45:36,442 --> 00:45:38,235
- Let's go, let's go!
- I'm so hungry.

1086
00:45:38,318 --> 00:45:40,571
- Finally!
- You must be hungry.

1087
00:45:40,654 --> 00:45:43,574
- Okay, it's self-serve. Dig in.
- Oh, it's buffet style.

1088
00:45:43,657 --> 00:45:45,159
- Wow. Amazing.
- That looks great.

1089
00:45:45,242 --> 00:45:47,453
- Whoa, that looks so good.
- Yeah.

1090
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:50,539
Enjoy the barbecue. Help yourselves.

1091
00:45:50,622 --> 00:45:51,707
Enjoy your meal.

1092
00:45:51,790 --> 00:45:55,085
Scoop some rice, and then you can
top it off with a fried egg.

1093
00:45:55,169 --> 00:45:56,879
Oh, eggs.

1094
00:45:56,962 --> 00:45:58,881
Can't go wrong with that. It's foolproof.

1095
00:45:58,964 --> 00:46:00,924
- I'm kind of feeling nervous.
- Yeah, of course you are.

1096
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:02,968
- What if it's bad?
- Here goes.

1097
00:46:03,051 --> 00:46:04,678
Wow, this looks so good.

1098
00:46:05,679 --> 00:46:07,264
Yeah, it looks delicious.

1099
00:46:07,347 --> 00:46:09,933
Refill coming right up.

1100
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:11,977
INSTANT MEAT REFILL

1101
00:46:12,060 --> 00:46:15,105
Have we got a show for you!

1102
00:46:15,189 --> 00:46:17,775
- That's a lot of rice.
- Did I take too much?

1103
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:19,485
PILED HIGH

1104
00:46:19,568 --> 00:46:21,945
Help yourself. Don't be shy with the meat.

1105
00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:24,239
- Okay, will do. Thank you so much.
- Copy that.

1106
00:46:24,323 --> 00:46:26,408
What time are we having dinner?

1107
00:46:26,492 --> 00:46:28,827
Huh? Sorry?

1108
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:29,912
Whenever you want.

1109
00:46:29,995 --> 00:46:32,706
No, I just want to adjust how much
I eat depending on the timing.

1110
00:46:32,790 --> 00:46:34,541
Don't adjust a thing.
Eat as much as you want.

1111
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:37,377
- We'll be cooking one way or another.
- Dinner will be served around 7:00.

1112
00:46:37,461 --> 00:46:38,796
Okay, so around 7:00.

1113
00:46:38,879 --> 00:46:41,757
At our B&B, we've got
all three meals covered.

1114
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:43,050
Don't worry.

1115
00:46:43,133 --> 00:46:44,468
JAE-SEOK'S B&B PROVIDES
THREE MEALS A DAY!

1116
00:46:45,469 --> 00:46:47,304
- This egg.
- Yeah.

1117
00:46:47,387 --> 00:46:49,097
- It's runny.
- Yeah, it is.

1118
00:46:49,181 --> 00:46:50,349
Wow.

1119
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:51,725
The meat's good!

1120
00:46:52,351 --> 00:46:53,560
Enjoy your meal.

1121
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:55,562
SOME OF THE GUESTS
SUDDENLY LEAVE

1122
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:58,857
Why are they leaving already?
Why are they walking out mid-meal?

1123
00:46:59,608 --> 00:47:00,692
KWANG-SOO IS DISPATCHED

1124
00:47:00,776 --> 00:47:02,778
Who left? Oh, for drinks?

1125
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:05,364
Let's get two and share. I want Fanta.

1126
00:47:05,447 --> 00:47:07,783
They went to get drinks.
They went to get drinks.

1127
00:47:07,866 --> 00:47:09,743
Oh, for drinks?
I thought they walked out on us.

1128
00:47:09,827 --> 00:47:11,119
FALSE ALARM

1129
00:47:12,246 --> 00:47:13,413
How's the food, Dong-geon?

1130
00:47:13,497 --> 00:47:15,457
- I haven't eaten yet.
- Oh, you haven't eaten yet.

1131
00:47:16,041 --> 00:47:17,334
Man, this meat.

1132
00:47:17,417 --> 00:47:18,544
PRAYS BEFORE EATING

1133
00:47:19,044 --> 00:47:20,921
THE MEAT COOKED BY HIS NUNA

1134
00:47:21,004 --> 00:47:23,090
- Wow, it's so good.
- Thanks for the food.

1135
00:47:23,715 --> 00:47:25,467
- Is it good?
- Yeah, for real.

1136
00:47:25,551 --> 00:47:27,386
- Oh, thank goodness.
- I mean it.

1137
00:47:27,469 --> 00:47:28,679
It's good.

1138
00:47:28,762 --> 00:47:30,013
Mmm.

1139
00:47:32,766 --> 00:47:34,977
Is there anything you'd like for dinner?

1140
00:47:35,060 --> 00:47:36,228
- Meat.
- Yeah, meat.

1141
00:47:36,311 --> 00:47:37,354
You want more meat?

1142
00:47:37,437 --> 00:47:39,606
MORE MEAT?

1143
00:47:39,690 --> 00:47:41,817
- Some soup would be nice.
- Soup. Thought so.

1144
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:44,027
- Ooh. Doenjang-jjigae too!
- All right.

1145
00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:45,571
Oh, kimchi-jjigae.

1146
00:47:46,363 --> 00:47:48,156
They're saying it'd be nice
to have some soup.

1147
00:47:48,240 --> 00:47:50,701
Sure. That makes sense.
Okay, everyone. Listen up.

1148
00:47:50,784 --> 00:47:54,955
Since we had meat for lunch, we should
have something brothy for dinner, right?

1149
00:47:55,038 --> 00:47:57,499
- Yes, sounds good.
- Yeah!

1150
00:47:57,583 --> 00:48:00,502
- Wow, the weather is so nice today.
- It really is.

1151
00:48:00,586 --> 00:48:02,254
- It's so nice.
- Wow, what a day.

1152
00:48:02,337 --> 00:48:04,214
Man, it's so beautiful out.

1153
00:48:05,007 --> 00:48:06,800
THE FOOD TASTES GOOD

1154
00:48:06,884 --> 00:48:08,343
Anyone want more meat?

1155
00:48:09,052 --> 00:48:11,138
- Oh, this is great. Have another egg.
- Oh, thanks.

1156
00:48:11,221 --> 00:48:12,514
The meat is really good.

1157
00:48:12,598 --> 00:48:13,891
- Yeah.
- It's good?

1158
00:48:13,974 --> 00:48:15,726
Who made the marinade?

1159
00:48:15,809 --> 00:48:17,352
The marinade…

1160
00:48:17,936 --> 00:48:21,273
Well, I mean, you know,
Ye-eun here is on a cooking show, and…

1161
00:48:21,356 --> 00:48:23,525
- Right.
- …you know what that means.

1162
00:48:23,609 --> 00:48:25,777
- What are we doing after lunch?
- Sorry?

1163
00:48:25,861 --> 00:48:27,905
- What's after lunch?
- Oh, after lunch.

1164
00:48:27,988 --> 00:48:31,783
First, we'll give you some free time,
let you relax a bit, and digest.

1165
00:48:31,867 --> 00:48:34,286
- Okay.
- We'll have around one activity a day.

1166
00:48:34,369 --> 00:48:35,579
It's nothing special.

1167
00:48:35,662 --> 00:48:37,664
But we have some surprises in store.

1168
00:48:38,290 --> 00:48:40,709
Hey, Dong-geon. Dong-geon.

1169
00:48:40,792 --> 00:48:42,628
- Don't talk to him.
- How was it?

1170
00:48:43,253 --> 00:48:45,672
- How was it? Be honest with me.
- It was fun.

1171
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:46,798
- Huh?
- It was fun.

1172
00:48:46,882 --> 00:48:48,342
It… It was fun?

1173
00:48:48,425 --> 00:48:51,887
- He's asking about the food.
- Oh, the food. It was delicious.

1174
00:48:51,970 --> 00:48:54,890
I hear he was just
as surprised as we were.

1175
00:48:54,973 --> 00:48:57,184
He signed up for the show by himself.

1176
00:48:57,267 --> 00:48:59,269
His sister was announced after.

1177
00:48:59,353 --> 00:49:01,104
- Yeah, that's right. I had no idea.
- Exactly.

1178
00:49:01,188 --> 00:49:04,191
- If you'd known, would you have signed up?
- Of course not.

1179
00:49:04,274 --> 00:49:06,193
It's the same for her.

1180
00:49:06,276 --> 00:49:08,320
I'm sure she feels the same way.

1181
00:49:08,904 --> 00:49:10,906
It's nice to see you're enjoying the food.

1182
00:49:10,989 --> 00:49:12,324
- It's so good.
- Oh, really?

1183
00:49:12,407 --> 00:49:14,409
- It tastes great.
- Thank you.

1184
00:49:14,493 --> 00:49:16,370
- It was all a team effort.
- I feel so proud.

1185
00:49:16,453 --> 00:49:20,415
Seeing you enjoy the food we made
brings us such joy, you have no idea.

1186
00:49:20,499 --> 00:49:22,084
Now then, lunch?

1187
00:49:23,460 --> 00:49:25,420
- Solved.
- Solved.

1188
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:29,049
It was great.

1189
00:49:29,132 --> 00:49:31,468
- Now start dinner!
- Let's go!

1190
00:49:32,135 --> 00:49:33,303
HOW WAS THE MEAL?

1191
00:49:33,387 --> 00:49:36,223
- Satisfactory. Yeah, I'm satisfied.
- Did you vote yet?

1192
00:49:37,057 --> 00:49:39,434
You can choose "unsatisfactory"
if you'd like.

1193
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:41,770
But I mean, he's standing right there.

1194
00:49:42,562 --> 00:49:43,605
It was good.

1195
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:47,859
- I'm voting blue!
- We vote blue, we vote blue!

1196
00:49:47,943 --> 00:49:50,362
Geez, these kids are too adorable!

1197
00:49:50,445 --> 00:49:52,197
They all said it was satisfactory.

1198
00:49:52,280 --> 00:49:54,658
- Oh, yeah.
- Hey, there's one yellow.

1199
00:49:56,827 --> 00:49:58,787
THE GUESTS ENJOYED THE FOOD
DESPITE IT BEING A BIT SALTY

1200
00:49:58,870 --> 00:50:00,622
So-so.

1201
00:50:00,706 --> 00:50:04,042
It was a little bit… a little bit salty.
The sauce, I mean.

1202
00:50:04,126 --> 00:50:05,836
It's a bit salty, right?

1203
00:50:05,919 --> 00:50:07,421
- Just a bit.
- A bit.

1204
00:50:07,504 --> 00:50:08,630
Even so,

1205
00:50:08,714 --> 00:50:12,467
I could tell it was made with
so much care, so I really enjoyed it.

1206
00:50:12,551 --> 00:50:15,554
THE GUESTS ENJOYED THE FOOD
DESPITE IT BEING A BIT SALTY

1207
00:50:15,637 --> 00:50:17,472
- We should have a bite.
- I want some.

1208
00:50:17,556 --> 00:50:20,350
STAFF LUNCH BREAK

1209
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:24,354
Whoa, I feel like I'm gonna faint.

1210
00:50:24,438 --> 00:50:26,648
- My mind's gone blank.
- All I care about is the food.

1211
00:50:26,732 --> 00:50:28,817
- Seriously.
- I'm totally drained.

1212
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:30,527
- Yeah, same.
- It's so draining.

1213
00:50:31,403 --> 00:50:32,529
Oh, boy. Phew!

1214
00:50:32,612 --> 00:50:36,033
FINALLY SITTING DOWN
AFTER THREE HOURS

1215
00:50:39,119 --> 00:50:40,287
Thank you for the food.

1216
00:50:43,665 --> 00:50:44,875
I feel better already.

1217
00:50:44,958 --> 00:50:46,084
JAE-SEOK TAKES A BITE

1218
00:50:46,168 --> 00:50:47,294
(VERY TASTY) (DELICIOUS)

1219
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:50,422
AND TOPS UP ON HYDRATION

1220
00:50:53,967 --> 00:50:56,136
- Guys, this is good.
- It's good.

1221
00:50:57,137 --> 00:50:59,222
- Wow, it's really good.
- So hungry.

1222
00:50:59,306 --> 00:51:00,682
- It's great.
- Me too.

1223
00:51:00,766 --> 00:51:02,893
But remember what I said earlier?

1224
00:51:02,976 --> 00:51:06,938
If we start off with something this good,
what do we serve next?

1225
00:51:07,022 --> 00:51:08,523
For dinner?

1226
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:09,775
Yeah.

1227
00:51:09,858 --> 00:51:11,401
What do we have written on there?

1228
00:51:11,485 --> 00:51:12,694
Let's see.

1229
00:51:13,361 --> 00:51:17,199
B&B DINER TODAY'S MENU,
MENU WISH LIST

1230
00:51:17,282 --> 00:51:19,701
We've got to take at least one suggestion.

1231
00:51:19,785 --> 00:51:22,662
Hyung, it says samgyeopsal, malatang,

1232
00:51:22,746 --> 00:51:23,997
muksabal,

1233
00:51:24,081 --> 00:51:26,374
budae-jjigae and sujebi.

1234
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:28,293
- Okay, budae-jjigae.
- For real?

1235
00:51:28,376 --> 00:51:29,669
No, but budae-jjigae is…

1236
00:51:29,753 --> 00:51:32,172
But you know what you're really good at
is kimchi-jjigae.

1237
00:51:32,255 --> 00:51:35,217
Hyung, I'm dead serious
right now. I-- I just can't.

1238
00:51:35,300 --> 00:51:36,301
KWANG-SOO'S KIMCHI-JJIGAE

1239
00:51:36,384 --> 00:51:38,845
- We can add some ham to it.
- I think that's all we need.

1240
00:51:38,929 --> 00:51:41,598
Do we need anything else?
Should I make gyeran-mari?

1241
00:51:43,725 --> 00:51:44,810
Man…

1242
00:51:45,977 --> 00:51:47,229
You and your eggs.

1243
00:51:47,854 --> 00:51:50,732
- I'm just all about the eggs.
- Were you an egg in a past life?

1244
00:51:51,441 --> 00:51:53,610
You're the main chef for dinner tonight.
And you.

1245
00:51:53,693 --> 00:51:55,320
- Gyeran-mari.
- Gyeran-mari.

1246
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:57,572
My heart just skipped a beat.

1247
00:51:57,656 --> 00:51:59,658
Wait. Who's that over there?

1248
00:51:59,741 --> 00:52:01,409
Oh, Kwang-soo's castmate.

1249
00:52:01,493 --> 00:52:03,328
He was in that movie with you.

1250
00:52:03,411 --> 00:52:05,205
- Hello.
- Hello. Oh!

1251
00:52:05,288 --> 00:52:07,290
- Hey, man!
- Whoa!

1252
00:52:07,374 --> 00:52:10,043
- Do you know each other?
- We shot <i>The Pirates </i>together.

1253
00:52:10,127 --> 00:52:11,294
- Yeah.
- Hey, man.

1254
00:52:11,378 --> 00:52:12,963
- Hello.
- How have you been?

1255
00:52:13,046 --> 00:52:14,923
- Welcome aboard.
- Thank you.

1256
00:52:15,006 --> 00:52:16,466
- Right over here.
- Hello.

1257
00:52:17,717 --> 00:52:19,427
Wow, the sky's lookin' pretty.

1258
00:52:19,511 --> 00:52:21,304
JOO EUN-TAE: ACTOR
LEE JAE-SEONG: ACTOR

1259
00:52:22,180 --> 00:52:24,599
STARING

1260
00:52:24,683 --> 00:52:28,103
Guys, we gotta keep the show moving.
That alone is stressful.

1261
00:52:28,854 --> 00:52:32,190
All they've done is arrive,
unpack and eat. That's it.

1262
00:52:32,274 --> 00:52:34,192
Some walking around too.

1263
00:52:34,276 --> 00:52:36,278
Let's do that quiz game later.

1264
00:52:36,361 --> 00:52:39,030
- We'll tell them about it in a second.
- Okay.

1265
00:52:39,114 --> 00:52:41,074
- The Cushion Quiz!
- Yay!

1266
00:52:41,158 --> 00:52:42,325
Correct!

1267
00:52:42,409 --> 00:52:44,786
All right!

1268
00:52:44,870 --> 00:52:45,912
Correct!

1269
00:52:45,996 --> 00:52:47,414
YU B&B'S FIRST ACTIVITY

1270
00:52:47,497 --> 00:52:49,833
It's finally time for today's activity.

1271
00:52:49,916 --> 00:52:52,169
Okay, let's gather in the gymnasium
around three o'clock.

1272
00:52:52,252 --> 00:52:53,503
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

1273
00:52:58,258 --> 00:53:00,427
Should we do the dishes now?

1274
00:53:01,303 --> 00:53:04,598
We'd better get some
of it done now. I'll take care of them.

1275
00:53:05,265 --> 00:53:07,809
For ingredients? Who's buying them?

1276
00:53:07,893 --> 00:53:09,811
Another grocery run?

1277
00:53:09,895 --> 00:53:11,688
Later, at three o'clock.

1278
00:53:11,771 --> 00:53:14,482
- But if we go out to buy the ingredients…
- We have kimchi.

1279
00:53:14,566 --> 00:53:17,319
Oh, but we need coffee too.
They're gonna want coffee.

1280
00:53:17,402 --> 00:53:18,737
Oh, coffee…

1281
00:53:21,406 --> 00:53:22,657
Can you go buy some?

1282
00:53:22,741 --> 00:53:24,159
Today?

1283
00:53:24,242 --> 00:53:26,119
We have to buy it today? Wait.

1284
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:28,830
Should I make the announcement first?
That we'll meet at 3:00?

1285
00:53:28,914 --> 00:53:31,791
I don't know about that.
3:00 might be too early.

1286
00:53:31,875 --> 00:53:34,294
- We only have 30 minutes. Yeah, 30…
- It makes no sense.

1287
00:53:34,377 --> 00:53:36,296
- We need to rest too.
- Hyung, just five minutes.

1288
00:53:36,379 --> 00:53:39,007
Seriously… I mean, we haven't
even been able to sit down.

1289
00:53:39,090 --> 00:53:41,134
We're kings too.
Is that how you treat a king?

1290
00:53:41,218 --> 00:53:43,136
- My apologies.
- We're working like dogs!

1291
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:45,138
- What do you mean, we're kings?
- Hold on. The guests are coming.

1292
00:53:46,389 --> 00:53:48,266
- He sounds upset.
- Yeah.

1293
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:51,311
Okay, let's not let
our internal complaints get out

1294
00:53:51,394 --> 00:53:53,230
- and reach our guests, shall we?
- Got it.

1295
00:53:53,313 --> 00:53:55,440
Let's make this promise
to each other, okay?

1296
00:53:55,523 --> 00:53:58,652
Criticizing is fine between us.
But the guests shouldn't have to hear it.

1297
00:53:58,735 --> 00:54:01,613
Of course. I'll keep that in mind.
We at least need time to brush our teeth.

1298
00:54:01,696 --> 00:54:02,822
Forget about it.

1299
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:04,491
NO BRUSHING TEETH

1300
00:54:04,574 --> 00:54:07,911
- When you talk, talk like this.
- Oh, come on.

1301
00:54:07,994 --> 00:54:10,580
I've still got pork stuck in my teeth.

1302
00:54:10,664 --> 00:54:12,582
I have to brush my teeth right now.

1303
00:54:12,666 --> 00:54:15,168
- No time for brushing. No brushing.
- No brushing.

1304
00:54:15,252 --> 00:54:16,711
A B&B THAT WON'T EVEN GIVE YOU
TIME TO BRUSH YOUR TEETH

1305
00:54:16,795 --> 00:54:18,255
- What about this?
- Yeah?

1306
00:54:18,338 --> 00:54:21,091
Let's have the losing team
later do all the dishes.

1307
00:54:21,174 --> 00:54:23,426
- If there's around ten people…
- Right.

1308
00:54:23,510 --> 00:54:25,553
The more people there are,
the faster it goes.

1309
00:54:25,637 --> 00:54:27,305
- Ye-eun.
- The more, the faster.

1310
00:54:27,389 --> 00:54:29,975
How about we bring Dong-geon
and his friends over?

1311
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:31,851
Nice!

1312
00:54:33,436 --> 00:54:35,146
Okay, sounds good.

1313
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:37,190
Hey, Dong-geon!

1314
00:54:37,274 --> 00:54:39,150
- Hey, Dong-geon!
- Yeah?

1315
00:54:39,234 --> 00:54:41,236
- Can you and your friends come over?
- Coming.

1316
00:54:41,319 --> 00:54:42,320
- Oh, boy.
- Thank you.

1317
00:54:42,404 --> 00:54:44,489
SUCCESSFULLY LURED

1318
00:54:44,572 --> 00:54:46,324
It's kind of adorable seeing them play.

1319
00:54:46,408 --> 00:54:49,619
Hey guys, our schedule is
a bit tight today.

1320
00:54:49,703 --> 00:54:51,037
So if you don't mind,

1321
00:54:51,121 --> 00:54:55,000
since it looks like the three of you
aren't doing much important right now…

1322
00:54:55,083 --> 00:54:57,043
- You said we had free time.
- Oh, I sure did.

1323
00:54:57,127 --> 00:54:58,795
So why don't you help, uh, do the dishes?

1324
00:54:58,878 --> 00:55:00,588
- Sure, we can help.
- Let's go!

1325
00:55:00,672 --> 00:55:02,799
He did offer to help
with the dishes earlier.

1326
00:55:02,882 --> 00:55:05,593
- All right, this is great.
- Oh, then you guys can do the dishes.

1327
00:55:05,677 --> 00:55:06,970
We've got so much else to do.

1328
00:55:07,053 --> 00:55:08,888
- We do.
- All good, we got it.

1329
00:55:08,972 --> 00:55:10,807
- You stay here and help out.
- Okay, sounds good.

1330
00:55:11,766 --> 00:55:13,727
SCRUB, SCRUB

1331
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:21,026
THE STAFF STARTS CLEANING UP TOO

1332
00:55:21,109 --> 00:55:23,570
Should we help with the stuff
they put down there?

1333
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:25,238
- Help them how?
- I don't know.

1334
00:55:25,322 --> 00:55:27,949
- Don't they need to be washed?
- Give it to us. We'll do it.

1335
00:55:28,033 --> 00:55:30,327
What are you doing?
No, seriously, we're fine!

1336
00:55:30,410 --> 00:55:32,162
- Oh, come on.
- Come on, just this one. Please?

1337
00:55:32,245 --> 00:55:33,246
It's just one thing.

1338
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:35,790
This is the last time you're helping,
you hear me?

1339
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:38,877
- Jae-seok's B&B isn't like that, okay?
- Okay, got it.

1340
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:40,754
IT REALLY ISN'T, BUT?

1341
00:55:40,837 --> 00:55:42,839
It's easier when we all pitch in.

1342
00:55:42,922 --> 00:55:44,883
Right, it's all about
doing things together.

1343
00:55:44,966 --> 00:55:47,969
- Oh, please. Don't do this, guys.
- I'll give it a go.

1344
00:55:48,053 --> 00:55:50,972
Where on earth did you find guests
that are such angels?

1345
00:55:51,890 --> 00:55:54,184
THE STAFF ARE WORKING HARD TOO

1346
00:55:54,934 --> 00:55:58,355
THE CLEANUP IS ALMOST DONE

1347
00:56:00,523 --> 00:56:02,359
Working together is faster, huh?

1348
00:56:02,442 --> 00:56:04,319
I swear, next time,
we do it all ourselves.

1349
00:56:04,402 --> 00:56:07,614
All right everyone, let's all
gather around at half past.

1350
00:56:07,697 --> 00:56:10,909
Al right everyone, let's all gather around
at half past.

1351
00:56:10,992 --> 00:56:13,995
We'll have a discussion about what time
we all wanna get up in the morning.

1352
00:56:14,079 --> 00:56:16,164
- Got it.
- Yeah, sounds good.

1353
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:19,334
FOOD IS POWER
LET'S SCARF IT DOWN

1354
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:21,002
CURRENT TIME
40 MINUTES UNTIL GATHERING

1355
00:56:22,962 --> 00:56:24,130
DISHES FOR 22 PEOPLE: DONE

1356
00:56:24,214 --> 00:56:26,549
Hold on, let me go get the coffee first.

1357
00:56:28,426 --> 00:56:31,888
Hyung, while we're out picking that up,
should we buy dinner ingredients too?

1358
00:56:31,971 --> 00:56:33,765
You have to. You're the main chef,

1359
00:56:33,848 --> 00:56:36,518
and you're Mr. Eggs,
so the three of us should head out soon.

1360
00:56:36,601 --> 00:56:38,144
Tomorrow's breakfast? What about that?

1361
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:41,523
I bought some bread, so let's keep
breakfast simple with toast and cereal.

1362
00:56:41,606 --> 00:56:44,734
If we have a toaster,
we could make grilled cheese.

1363
00:56:44,818 --> 00:56:45,819
Sorry?

1364
00:56:45,902 --> 00:56:48,071
But toasters only make
two slices at a time.

1365
00:56:48,154 --> 00:56:51,783
Ye-eun, since your brother's here and all,
can you organize things for us?

1366
00:56:51,866 --> 00:56:53,368
- Me? Uh… Yes.
- Yeah, that all right?

1367
00:56:53,451 --> 00:56:55,412
- Good.
- I'll just use the bathroom first.

1368
00:56:55,495 --> 00:56:56,913
- Make it quick.
- Okay.

1369
00:56:56,996 --> 00:57:00,625
TO-DO LIST: GROCERY RUN FOR
DINNER & BREAKFAST, BUY COFFEE

1370
00:57:02,127 --> 00:57:04,421
How is this day going by so fast?

1371
00:57:06,297 --> 00:57:08,842
LOADS THERMOS DISPENSER
FOR THE COFFEE

1372
00:57:10,885 --> 00:57:13,721
Okay, everyone, I'll see you all at 3:30!

1373
00:57:13,805 --> 00:57:15,348
Okay!

1374
00:57:16,349 --> 00:57:18,726
Oh, boy. This is killing me.

1375
00:57:23,523 --> 00:57:27,193
OFF TO BUY COFFEE & GROCERIES

1376
00:57:27,277 --> 00:57:29,195
Oh!

1377
00:57:30,321 --> 00:57:31,865
I forgot the others.

1378
00:57:31,948 --> 00:57:33,867
FORGOT TO BRING MAIN CHEF
& MR. EGGS

1379
00:57:33,950 --> 00:57:35,410
Guess I have to turn back.

1380
00:57:36,119 --> 00:57:37,454
I'm so scatterbrained.

1381
00:57:37,537 --> 00:57:39,038
I must be possessed or something.

1382
00:57:39,122 --> 00:57:40,999
(U-TURN)

1383
00:57:41,082 --> 00:57:42,459
Hey, Kwang-soo!

1384
00:57:42,542 --> 00:57:43,668
Yes, Hyung?

1385
00:57:43,751 --> 00:57:45,462
- Hey, Woo-seok!
- Yep!

1386
00:57:45,545 --> 00:57:46,629
Let's go.

1387
00:57:46,713 --> 00:57:48,631
I loaded the coffee dispenser.

1388
00:57:53,011 --> 00:57:54,220
HEADING OUT FOR REAL

1389
00:57:54,304 --> 00:57:56,389
Just now, I loaded that thing in the car

1390
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:58,850
and just took off by myself
without thinking about it.

1391
00:57:58,933 --> 00:58:02,187
I got to here and suddenly went,
"Oh, I left them behind."

1392
00:58:02,270 --> 00:58:04,355
It's only day one. I'm worried for us.

1393
00:58:04,439 --> 00:58:06,524
I can't believe it's already 3:00 p.m.

1394
00:58:07,108 --> 00:58:10,612
THEY'RE ALREADY EXHAUSTED
AFTER LUNCH

1395
00:58:11,279 --> 00:58:13,156
This is kinda therapeutic in a way.

1396
00:58:14,699 --> 00:58:15,909
How so?

1397
00:58:16,784 --> 00:58:18,453
Because you can't think.

1398
00:58:18,536 --> 00:58:21,289
Ah, I see.
We really have no time to think, Woo-seok.

1399
00:58:21,372 --> 00:58:22,373
That's true.

1400
00:58:22,457 --> 00:58:24,083
Minced garlic, kimchi,

1401
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,002
ham, sausage.

1402
00:58:26,085 --> 00:58:28,463
THE ONLY THOUGHT ALLOWED:
GROCERIES

1403
00:58:28,546 --> 00:58:29,881
What do you think?

1404
00:58:29,964 --> 00:58:32,842
Should we make two different types
of gyeran-mari or just one?

1405
00:58:32,926 --> 00:58:34,761
And do we need any condiments?

1406
00:58:34,844 --> 00:58:38,181
Yeah, we need ketchup.
I swear, you blink, and it's time to eat.

1407
00:58:39,265 --> 00:58:43,269
So, on our way there, we'll drop off
that dispenser at the café…

1408
00:58:43,353 --> 00:58:45,647
- Okay.
- …ask for 20 liters of coffee, and…

1409
00:58:46,314 --> 00:58:47,524
Ah!

1410
00:58:47,607 --> 00:58:49,609
I hope they don't give us acidic coffee.

1411
00:58:50,193 --> 00:58:52,111
That's just your preference.

1412
00:58:52,904 --> 00:58:55,615
- Right, it's not just for me.
- You're making it sound like a crisis.

1413
00:58:55,698 --> 00:58:58,535
- We'll drop off the dispenser.
- Yeah, drop it off here.

1414
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:01,538
Hello. Hello.

1415
00:59:01,621 --> 00:59:03,248
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1416
00:59:03,331 --> 00:59:05,124
- Thank you.
- We can pick up the coffee later.

1417
00:59:05,208 --> 00:59:06,709
Okay, let's do that.

1418
00:59:06,793 --> 00:59:08,586
Do you think we should wear name tags?

1419
00:59:08,670 --> 00:59:09,963
Yes. What's your name?

1420
00:59:10,046 --> 00:59:11,881
- Jae-hyeong.
- Jae-hyeong.

1421
00:59:11,965 --> 00:59:13,299
Thank you.

1422
00:59:13,383 --> 00:59:14,842
Ji Dong-geon.

1423
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:21,266
Honey, come sit with me.

1424
00:59:21,933 --> 00:59:24,435
Oh, you two.
I'm so curious about your love story.

1425
00:59:25,853 --> 00:59:27,897
I'm so curious about everyone.

1426
00:59:29,023 --> 00:59:31,234
- Did the three of you come together?
- Yes.

1427
00:59:31,317 --> 00:59:33,444
- I gotta know.
- I don't wanna say.

1428
00:59:33,528 --> 00:59:34,779
Yeah, same.

1429
00:59:34,862 --> 00:59:36,739
- You three are siblings, right?
- Yeah.

1430
00:59:36,823 --> 00:59:37,907
Yeah, they're siblings.

1431
00:59:37,991 --> 00:59:39,951
They're siblings. One here, one there.

1432
00:59:40,034 --> 00:59:41,452
I have two brothers.

1433
00:59:41,536 --> 00:59:43,580
How are so close with your siblings?

1434
00:59:45,832 --> 00:59:47,083
- You're one of three too.
- Right.

1435
00:59:47,166 --> 00:59:48,793
- You're the eldest.
- We're totally…

1436
00:59:49,794 --> 00:59:52,380
- Are there any perks for us?
- I don't think there are any.

1437
00:59:53,798 --> 00:59:56,426
- Yeah, we don't have any.
- Honestly, there aren't any.

1438
00:59:56,509 --> 00:59:58,094
- Did you get the ham?
- We have it here.

1439
00:59:58,177 --> 01:00:00,096
We got it.
Kwang-soo, did you get the garlic?

1440
01:00:00,179 --> 01:00:02,390
I got the minced garlic.
We got everything.

1441
01:00:02,473 --> 01:00:04,559
Wait. Did you get the cereal?

1442
01:00:04,642 --> 01:00:06,311
- Oh, I forgot.
- Man…

1443
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:09,063
What kind of cereal should we get?

1444
01:00:09,147 --> 01:00:11,107
We should get a few different kinds.

1445
01:00:12,108 --> 01:00:14,569
Some people really like this stuff,
you know.

1446
01:00:14,652 --> 01:00:15,653
Uh…

1447
01:00:15,737 --> 01:00:17,196
HESITATES

1448
01:00:17,280 --> 01:00:20,700
Almond-free? Since some people
might have nut allergies.

1449
01:00:20,783 --> 01:00:22,577
TIME FLIES
WHILE HE'S IN A DILEMMA

1450
01:00:22,660 --> 01:00:24,162
Now we just need to get milk.

1451
01:00:24,245 --> 01:00:25,830
- Okay, okay. Milk?
- Yeah.

1452
01:00:25,913 --> 01:00:27,624
HESITATING AGAIN

1453
01:00:27,707 --> 01:00:29,584
Uh-oh. No lactose-free milk.

1454
01:00:31,586 --> 01:00:32,795
No lactose-free milk!

1455
01:00:32,879 --> 01:00:35,214
We should probably go
with regular milk then.

1456
01:00:35,298 --> 01:00:37,550
Right. Some people might… Wait.

1457
01:00:37,634 --> 01:00:39,594
- Oh, there's the lactose-free.
- This should work.

1458
01:00:39,677 --> 01:00:42,597
Why are we getting milk again?
Oh! For the cereal.

1459
01:00:45,433 --> 01:00:47,101
Is that everything?

1460
01:00:47,185 --> 01:00:48,186
Tuna, tuna!

1461
01:00:48,269 --> 01:00:50,104
- We need tuna. Tuna.
- Oh, shoot.

1462
01:00:50,188 --> 01:00:52,148
It won't taste the same
if we don't add tuna.

1463
01:00:52,231 --> 01:00:53,816
- Let's get the mild one then.
- Okay.

1464
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:55,401
Oh, we need ketchup.

1465
01:00:55,485 --> 01:00:56,903
Right, ketchup.

1466
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:58,780
- Now is that everything?
- That's everything.

1467
01:00:58,863 --> 01:01:00,406
They'll probably want some fruit.

1468
01:01:02,492 --> 01:01:04,577
- Huh?
- Try some of these.

1469
01:01:05,578 --> 01:01:07,747
This would be perfect
to leave out for everyone.

1470
01:01:07,830 --> 01:01:09,957
- Could we try one too, please?
- Sure.

1471
01:01:11,542 --> 01:01:13,461
Tasty, right? They're good.

1472
01:01:14,796 --> 01:01:16,297
Hey, let's get these.

1473
01:01:16,381 --> 01:01:17,757
- Let's get two.
- Two boxes.

1474
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:19,717
- Thank you, ma'am. Here.
- You're welcome.

1475
01:01:20,385 --> 01:01:23,429
Man, I really wanna go home.
Oh, I wanna go home so bad.

1476
01:01:24,055 --> 01:01:25,598
Oh, boy, Kwang-soo.

1477
01:01:25,682 --> 01:01:27,517
- Oh, Woo-seok.
- Yeah.

1478
01:01:27,600 --> 01:01:29,102
We gotta go pick up the coffee.

1479
01:01:29,185 --> 01:01:30,269
- Right.
- Yeah.

1480
01:01:30,353 --> 01:01:31,521
Thank you.

1481
01:01:31,604 --> 01:01:32,730
- Thank you.
- Yep.

1482
01:01:32,814 --> 01:01:33,981
THEY PICK UP THE COFFEE

1483
01:01:34,774 --> 01:01:38,194
Hey, get a load of my staff!
They really know what they're doing, huh?

1484
01:01:38,277 --> 01:01:40,071
- Okay, there we go.
- My goodness.

1485
01:01:40,154 --> 01:01:42,156
Time really flies out here, huh?

1486
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:43,866
It's already 4:00.

1487
01:01:43,950 --> 01:01:45,576
Should we call everyone over?

1488
01:01:45,660 --> 01:01:47,328
I don't think they're back yet.

1489
01:01:47,412 --> 01:01:48,621
Did they go far?

1490
01:01:48,705 --> 01:01:51,207
We said 3:30, but it's already 4:00.

1491
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:54,252
It takes around ten minutes, right?
From here?

1492
01:01:54,335 --> 01:01:56,838
- Right. What, what, what?
- Huh?

1493
01:01:58,423 --> 01:01:59,882
What, what, what?

1494
01:01:59,966 --> 01:02:01,050
It's leaking a bit.

1495
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:03,553
- A lot?
- No, just a little. It's fine.

1496
01:02:04,971 --> 01:02:06,889
So how should I make it?

1497
01:02:06,973 --> 01:02:09,642
Yeah, I guess a wok
is different from a frying pan.

1498
01:02:10,351 --> 01:02:13,521
- It's because we're going uphill. Whoa!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1499
01:02:13,604 --> 01:02:15,606
THIS TIME, THE LID ESCAPES

1500
01:02:15,690 --> 01:02:18,192
- No! No!
- Did it all spill?

1501
01:02:18,276 --> 01:02:20,570
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!
